

=Bio=

"Miles Fidelman is a Systems Architect, Entrepreneur, and Policy Analyst focused on applying the Internet to support new forms of organization. His 36-year career dates to the earliest days of the ARPANET and Internet. Along the way he has worked on defense information systems, led R&D efforts, built the non-profit Center for Civic Networking, built a web hosting business, and developed R&D programs for several small companies. He is currently a Founder and Principal of the Protocol Technologies Group, LLC - focusing on the development of application level protocols for operational coordination in mission-critical environments."


